This paper deals with sequence labeling tasks using neural models, which is a common topic in the natural language processing (NLP) field. Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes a new model and method for improving the scalability and accuracy of existing models, which involves machine learning techniques such as pruning and combining different types of LSTMs. This suggests that the paper may also be relevant to sub-categories such as cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper evaluates its proposed method on NLP tasks such as all-phrase chunking and named entity recognition (NER), which are also relevant to the cs.CL sub-category. There is also a possibility that the paper may be relevant to cs.CV (Computer Vision) if the proposed method can be applied to sequence labeling tasks in image or video data.
